OL,3,CWall Street tumbles as global stock
OL,4,Cmarket sell-off takes hold
OL,6,FLondon's blue-chip index - which
OL,7,Ftracks the shares of well-known and
OL,8,Ffinancially stable publicly traded
OL,9,Fcompanies - was 2.4% down after the
OL,10,Fopen on Monday falling 193 points to
OL,11,F7,982, in its sharpest fall since July
OL,12,Flast year.
OL,14,FStocks on Wall Street also plunged on
OL,15,FMonday, prompting concerns about a
OL,16,Frecession in the United States.
OL,18,FThe S&P 500 was down by 4% in early
OL,19,Ftrading, while Dow Jones Industrial
OL,20,FAverage was down 1,197 points, or 3%
OL,21,Fon Monday morning.
